Game rules are very important in any type of card game when everyone participates.
 For 3-card Lieng, you also need to understand how to calculate points to play confidently. Specifically,
 the Lieng test will have specific scoring methods as follows:

Wax: the strongest cards in this card game. They will be 3 cards with the same value but different suits, 
the value will be calculated from low to high from 2 to Ace.

Lieng: The 2nd highest card value for Lieng. It is a 3 card with consecutive values ​​that can be of different 
suits such as 6 - 7 - 8, 9 - 10 - J... The card with the highest value in this format is Q - K - Ace. 
If you have this type of card in your hand, playing 3-card Lien is too simple for you.
Lieng Dong Hoa (in many places it will be called Slut): The 3 cards the player is dealt are headed
 J, Q, K but not Lieng. These are picture cards without any order or rules.
If it does not fall into the above cases, 

we will have to calculate the total score of the 3 cards. In this case, cards 10, J, Q, K are counted as 
0 points, Aces are counted as 1 point. Points will be calculated in units if the total is 10.
